to create tags just prepend + sign before the tag name like so:
	task add +home +work Water the flowers
	executing task or task li will show you that tag
	each task can be associated with at least one project. note that a project in this context is just a plain-text attribute.
	task subproject can be accessed via the dot notation e.g. project.subproject 'add your text here'
	priority attributes specify the priority of the task[s].
	set editor env variable to whatever you choose in dot bashrc then when you do the command task <iD> edit, your editor will open the task ID for editing.
	note: installed taskd aka taskserver with yay
	You must specify the 'server' variable before attempting a server start, for example:
		taskd config server localhost:53589

	